          <avActivityComment>Avalanche danger above 1600 m is moderate, below that altitude danger is low. Main problem: gliding snow. On steep smooth slopes which have not yet discharged medium-sized glide-snow avalanches can trigger naturally in all aspects, esp. at 1600-2200 m. Zones beneath glide cracks should be avoided.&#13;
At altitudes above 2400 m, isolated snowdrifts can in addition be problematic. Danger zones where small to medium slabs can trigger by large additional loading occur on steep north-facing slopes.</avActivityComment>
